The article discusses the recent tragic death of Tyre Nichols, a son and father, at the hands of law enforcement officers. The author emphasizes the need to address the persistent issue of police misconduct and excessive use of force in America. They support President Biden's call for accountability and transparency and advocate for the passing of the George Floyd Justice in Policing Act. The author concludes by stating that in order to honor Nichols' memory and the memory of others who have suffered similar fates, the justice system must live up to its name.